  <h2>Beau: The easiest way to test your web APIs</h2>

  <pre><code>npm install -g beau</code></pre>
</div>

<div class="content">
  <section>
    <div class="description">
      <h1>Simple</h1>
      <p>Beau makes testing APIs easy. All it takes is a simple yaml configuration file. You can easily configure the request's method, payload, headers and params.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="example">
      <pre><code>endpoint: "https://example.com"

POST /posts:
  alias: post
  payload:
    hello: World</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>


  <section>
    <div class="description">
      <h1>Succinct</h1>
      <p>Make use of variables and defaults, don't repeat yourself.</p>
    </div>
      <div class="example">
        <pre><code>endpoint: "https://example.com"

environment:
  post: 1

defaults:
  headers:
    authentication: Bearer 123456

GET /posts/$env.post: post</code></pre>
      </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="description">
      <h1>Composable</h1>
      <p>Compose multiple requests together. You can mix and match requests to test whole workflows.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="example">
      <pre><code>endpoint: "https://example.com"

GET /session: session

POST /profile:
  alias: profile
  headers:
    authentication: Bearer $session.token
  payload:
    name: David</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="documentation">
    <h1>Simple as Pie.</h1>
    <p>Get started fast by checking out the <a href="/docs">Documentation</a>.</p>
  </div>
</div>


